T1  - The Use of the Compound Poisson in Pert
AU  - Parks, William H.
AU  - Ramsing, Kenneth D.
Y1  - 1969/04/01
PY  - 1969
DA  - 1969/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.15.8.B397
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.15.8.B397
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - B-397
EP  - B-402
VL  - 15
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The use of the normal or Beta distributions has become well established for PERT applications. The authors question whether the use of these standardized distributions yields the best answers in some cases and submits an alternative method of computing the critical path using a compound poisson distribution. This change requires adapting many of the PERT assumptions to the new distribution.
AB  - The use of the normal or Beta distributions has become well established for PERT applications. The authors question whether the use of these standardized distributions yields the best answers in some cases and submits an alternative method of computing the critical path using a compound poisson distribution. This change requires adapting many of the PERT assumptions to the new distribution.
